<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXY-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GALAXY PICKS UP PRACTICE PACE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Galaxy defender Danny Pena had his right knee
wrapped in ice during Wednesday's training session at Jackie
Robinson Field outside the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Pena explained that it was only a precaution and insists he'll
be fine for Sunday's playoff game against Colorado at Mile High
Stadium. The Galaxy beat the Rapids 3-0 Sunday to take a 1-0 lead
in the best-of-three Western Conference semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   Pena, normally the one to turn a lazy training session into a
war with his harsh comments, enjoyed what he observed from the
sidelines this time. There was shouting, hard tackles, and even a
brief scuffle between Clint Mathis and Ezra Hendrickson _ though it
was all taken with the right attitude.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love it when the intensity level is like this,'' said Pena.
``You saw a playoff practice right here. I just wish I could have
been in there with them.''
</P>
<P>
   Defender Greg Vanney said there is a different feeling during
the playoffs this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It all comes down to this team being focused,'' said Vanney.
``It's something that hasn't been here in the past.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't win a playoff game 3-0 with 10 players unless you're
training like this. This is how you become a championship team.
This is how it is in Europe, with people battling for their spots
every day. It's not how long you practice but the intensity and
effort you give. I think today was a good sign of what lies
ahead.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Weather or not: While the Galaxy continues to train in the
mid-day heat, Schmid is not concerned with the forecast in Denver.
There was snow and temperatures in the 40s last weekend, and Sunday
could be more of the same.
</P>
<P>
   ``The forecast can change in a day there,'' said Schmid. ``I saw
one forecast where it was supposed to be in the 70s this weekend.
Then I saw another that said it would be in the 40s.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had a buddy who was up there for some games last weekend. He
said when he landed Saturday, it was 86 and the next day it was 43.
So, we've got to be prepared for anything. At least we're playing
during the day and not at night.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Hermosillo update: Galaxy striker Carlos Hermosillo gave a
thumbs up when asked if he was ready to start. Hermosillo missed
Sunday's opening playoff game with a bruised knee.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was always the plan to rest Carlos and play him in this
game,'' Schmid said.
</P>
</TEXT>
