   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ The first rule of ``Flight Club''
is you don't talk about ``Flight Club.'' Flight Club meets in the
middle of the day at the Sony Metreon's 11- screen cineplex, within
walking distance of most of the office buildings in San Francisco.
I'm sitting with a few dozen escapee office workers, mostly male,
watching Brad Pitt and Ed Norton kick some yuppie butt in this
film. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ How often can I forget that
times change and ``market forces'' dictate when and how? When San
Francisco radio station KDFC-FM announced it would not carry the
1999-2000 ``Live from the Met'' opera season, I was as angry as
anybody. By STEPHANIE SALTER.
</P>
