<P>
   Editors, news editors, features editors:
</P>
<P>
   We strongly commend to your attention an investigative series,
``Falling From the Sky,'' from  &UR; The Dayton (Ohio) Daily News &LR; , a
Cox newspaper, which will be distributed by our partner
organization,  &UR; Cox News Service &LR; , to clients of  &UR; The New York Times
News Service &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   The six-day series, which begins Sunday, Oct. 24, explores the
recent rise in military air crashes. The Dayton investigation
concludes that military aircraft are often pressed into service
despite known safety problems.
</P>
<P>
   A similar investigation by The Dayton Daily News of the military
health-care system earned the paper a Pulitzer Prize in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Papers with space constraints should consider running the first
installment alone, which summarizes the findings of the entire
series.
