r l BC-PARENTING-BOX-$ADV24-     10-21 0310
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PARENTING-BOX-$ADV24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EZZO VS LEACH: TO SPANK, OR NOT TO SPANK?
 &HT;    With BRITAIN-PARENTING-$ADV24.
 &HT;    Moving in both (i) International and (l) Lifestyle categories.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., Oct. 24 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SHELLEY EMLING 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service(at) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GARY AND ANNE MARIE EZZO:
</P>
<P>
   Founded a parenting ministry based in Simi Valley, Calif. called
Growing Families International. The Web site is www.gfi.org. Gary
Ezzo co-authored the books ``On Becoming Babywise'' and ``Babywise
II.'' More than 1.5 million parents have used the Ezzos Bible-based
curricula in churches around the world since 1989.
</P>
<P>
   They advise parents, among other things, to:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Toilet train children between the age of 18 and 24 months.
After the children are two and a half years old, they should be
required to clean up after themselves, even their soiled clothing.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Spanking, or chastisement, can start at 18 months. The weapon
shouldn't be too stiff or unbending. The Ezzos say a rubber spatula
would work.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Feed babies on a schedule to reduce colic, or extreme
fussiness.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Make children address adults as ``Mr.'' and ``Mrs.''
</P>
<P>
   PENELOPE LEACH:
</P>
<P>
   A British psychologist and author of several parenting guides.
Her most popular book is ``Your Baby and Child'' published in 1977
and updated in 1997. Her other books include ``Babyhood'' and
``Children First.''
</P>
<P>
   She advises parents to:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Kidproof their house rather than swat a toddler who fiddles
with the stereo.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Never spank, but use positive discipline. In other words,
praise children for doing right, rather than punish them for doing
wrong.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Feed babies on demand.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Provide one-on-one care to their children at least for the
first 18 months.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
