<SLUG> BC-COL-BIG12-VENUES-TEX </SLUG>
 
Big 12 sets championship venues 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIMMY BURCH 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
DALLAS _ For the first time since establishing Fort Worth-Dallas as
its base of operations when the league was created, Big 12
officials will host some of its highest-profile championship events
in its own back yard.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Big 12 board of directors, composed of presidents and
chancellors from the member schools, approved proposals Wednesday
to settle future championships in football, men's basketball and
women's basketball at area venues. The first championship event in
Fort Worth-Dallas will be the 2001 football title game, to be
played at Texas Stadium in Irving.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, the under-construction American Airlines Center in
Dallas will play host to the men's basketball tournament in 2003
and 2004, with the women's event to be played during the same
seasons at Reunion Arena.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Weiberg, Big 12 commissioner, said The Ballpark in
Arlington remains under consideration as a host site for at least
one future conference baseball tournament. But those negotiations
will not be finalized until next month, Weiberg said. No new
agreements regarding baseball sites were announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Weiberg cited ``a real desire and intent to try some new
locations'' as a factor in administrators' decisions to bring
championship events to Fort Worth-Dallas. He also confirmed that
the winning bids offered the best financial deals for the Big 12,
but declined to cite specifics.
</P>
<P>
   The selection of Texas Stadium as host site for the 2001
football game came in conjunction with the announcement that the
2000 game would be played at Arrowhead Stadium in Kansas City, Mo.
League officials also voted to continue rotating the football game
between northern and southern sites through 2003, with venues for
the 2002 (northern) and 2003 (southern) games to be determined.
</P>
<P>
   In selecting open-air stadiums to host the next two football
championship games, league officials allow the possibility of
adverse weather conditions to impact the outcome for the first
time. The first four football championship games rotated between
the TWA Dome in St. Louis (1996, 1998) and the Alamodome in San
Antonio (1997, 1999).
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, we're taking some risk in regard to the weather,''
Weiberg said. ``We gave that a considerable amount of discussion.
But there was a comfort level ... in knowing those stadiums can
support the games and offer our best financial situations.''
</P>
<P>
   As part of the bid process, Big 12 officials were offered the
opportunity to play the 2001 game at Texas Stadium or the Cotton
Bowl. Weiberg said Texas Stadium was selected because it offered a
greater ``showcase'' opportunity and administrators consider it ``a
better football-playing facility, at this point.''
</P>
<P>
   In selecting Dallas to hold basketball tournaments in 2003 and
2004, Big 12 officials broke with tradition. Since the league began
competition during 1996-97 school year, all basketball tournaments
have been played in Kansas City, where the men's event is a
perpetual sellout. Weiberg said administrators considered it vital
to keep the men's and women's tournaments in the same city and
viewed moving the event to Dallas as an opportunity to create
interest in a market that was slow to embrace the Southwest
Conference basketball tournament during its waning years.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't think the Big 12 tournament is the SWC tournament. We
think with the quality of basketball we'll bring to Dallas, the
event will be successful,'' Weiberg said.  &QL; 
Big 12 championship venues With agreements announced Wednesday, Big
12 officials have settled on championship venues for multiple years
in football and basketball. Below is a breakdown of where upcoming
championships will be played: School year Football Basketball (M&AMP;W)
Baseball 1999-2000 San Antonio Kansas City Oklahoma City 2000-2001
Kansas City Kansas City TBA 2001-2002 Irving (Texas Stadium) Kansas
City TBA 2002-2003 North Site (TBA) Dallas TBA 2003-2004 South Site
(TBA) Dallas TBA 2004-2005 TBA Kansas City TBA nn
</P>
