<HEADLINE>
IRS FINDS A MONEY POT IN THE TEXAS LOTTERY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ How much money has the Internal Revenue Service taken
in from Texas lottery winnings during 1998?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.H., Arlington.MDNM/, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ During calendar year 1998, the Internal Revenue Service
collected $96.8 million from Lotto Texas, according to the Texas
Lottery Commission.
</P>
<P>
   This figure represents 28 percent of the winnings from prizes of
$599 or more. The taxes for those prizes are withheld automatically
before the rest is paid to winners.
</P>
<P>
   For more information about the Texas Lottery, call (800)
375-6886 or visit the World Wide Web site www.txlottery.org.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I write to Russell Crowe? I'm 76 years old,
and this is the first time I've been in love since I saw Nelson
Eddy when I was a child.
</P>
<P>
   _ D.L., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to Crowe in care of International Creative
Management, 8942 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   Crowe, 35, was born in New Zealand to parents who were set
caterers and grew up around the entertainment industry. At age 6,
he appeared on the Australian TV series ``Spyforce,'' and from 1986
to 1988 he toured with the ``Rocky Horror Show'' in New Zealand and
Australia.
</P>
<P>
   After winning Australian acting awards for his role in ``Romper
Stomper,'' Crowe was cast in Sharon Stone's Western ``The Quick and
the Dead.'' Subsequent film credits include ``Mystery, Alaska,''
``Gladiator,'' ``Virtuosity'' and ``L.A. Confidential.''
</P>
<P>
   A more offbeat project is the band 30 Odd Foot of Grunts, which
includes Crowe and four musicians with whom he has performed since
they were teens. The group's current CD, ``Gaslight,'' is available
for $15 from Carys Filmworks in care of Ernst and Young, 1999
Avenue of the Stars, Suite 2200, Los Angeles, CA 90067-6102.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Who played Joey on the miniseries ``Streets of
Laredo,'' and what else has he been in?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The role was played by Alexis Cruz, an actor and improv
comedian who often appears on ``Touched By an Angel'' and the
``Stargate SG-1'' TV series. His film credits include ``Why Do
Fools Fall in Love'' and ``Stargate.''
</P>
<P>
   Cruz, who turned 25 on Sept. 29, was born in the Bronx, attended
the New York City High School for the Performing Arts and graduated
from Boston University. From 1986 to 1990, he was a ``Sesame
Street'' cast member.
</P>
<P>
   You can write to him in care of the Abrams Artist Agency, 9200
Sunset Blvd., Suite 1130, Los Angeles, CA 90069.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
