<HEADLINE>
`MEN CRY BULLETS': HE PUTS ON HIS DRESS ONE LEG AT A TIME 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds: Production notes are at end of review)  
 (af)  
 By ANITA GATES   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The best part of ``Men Cry Bullets'' is not when Gloria's blond
debutante cousin chases Gloria's pet pig, Jack, with an ax. The
best part is when Gloria, having learned of the slaughter, leaps
onto the dining room table and embraces the pork roast, sobbing,
``I'm a terrible mother.''
</P>
<P>
   Most of ``Men Cry Bullets,'' a muddled film with John Waters
aspirations, is not about animals, motherhood or vegetarianism,
however. It is, says Tamara Hernandez, its writer, director and
co-producer, a message about domestic violence, told with the
gender roles reversed to make its point.
</P>
<P>
   Billy (Steven Nelson) is the ingenue and a virgin, and Gloria
(Honey Lauren) is the seducer who grabs Billy's crotch and murmurs,
``You know you want it; you wouldn't be here if you didn't want
it,'' as he tearfully succumbs. And although this is largely inept
filmmaking, that scene has a flicker of power.
</P>
<P>
   Both the main characters often dress in drag, although not
particularly attractive drag. Lydia, the cousin (``I'm a debutante.
I've got dozens of dresses like this''), is played by Jeri Ryan,
best known as the predominantly alien character named Seven of Nine
on ``Star Trek: Voyager,'' and she does have screen presence.
</P>
<P>
   Other than that, the film just wanders around confused, trying
to pass for post-modern, throwing in a menage a trois fueled by
possibly poisoned wine and proudly showing off the other acts at
the club where Billy works: a man who lifts weights with chains
attached to his nipples and a woman who eats a huge plateful of
live worms.
</P>
<P>
   ``Men Cry Bullets'' opens Friday at the Angelika Film Center in
Manhattan. It includes profuse profanity, sexual situations, full
frontal male nudity, partial female nudity, animal murder, gunshots
and a strangling.
</P>
<P>
   PRODUCTION NOTES
</P>
<P>
   `MEN CRY BULLETS'
</P>
<P>
   Written and directed by Tamara Hernandez; director of
photography, Michael Grady; edited by Scott Balcerek and Garth
Grinde; music by Woodrow Jackson, Ivan Knight and Forest Dunn;
production designers, Ivana Letica and Regina Acuna; produced by
Harry Ralston and Ms. Hernandez; released by Phaedra Cinema.
Running time: 106 minutes. This film is not rated.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Steven Nelson (Billy), Honey Lauren (Gloria), Jeri Ryan
(Lydia), Michael Mangiamele (Paper Boy), Harry Ralston (Freddy
Fishnets) and Bob Sherer (Bootser). &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-21-99 1610EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
