 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE SPORTS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These sports stories for release Friday, October 22, 1999, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   WORLD SERIES
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ROCKER _ ATLANTA _ Braves reliever John Rocker has become
talk of baseball in the postseason. His comments about some New
York Mets fans drew national media attention in the NLCS and his
automobile accident Tuesday also kept him in the news. Despite his
off-the-field antics, Rocker has been the team's most successful
reliever on the field. His trademark sprint from the bullpen has
often led to overpowering performances on the mound, as witnessed
by two saves against the Mets. But who is the real John Rocker and
what makes him tick? (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RIVERA _ He's not as vocal as Braves reliever John Rocker,
but Yankee closer Mariano Rivera has been more dominating in the
postseason. Rivera hasn't allowed an earned run in five postseason
games this season and has the lowest ERA (0.70) in postseason
history. On a roster filled with All-Star pitchers, Rivera might be
the most valuable Yankee heading into the World Series. (Stinson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH _ We sit down with Georgia Tech coach George O'Leary
to ask him why he thinks the team is struggling and what he plans
to do to answer the questions Tech has raised with its play. We'll
find out what kind of changes he's thinking of making, or will
make, in an effort to stem those struggles. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA-PICKS _Georgia feature: The defense leads the SEC in
interceptions with 15. And though it has been criticized for its
overall play, the interceptions show that it is fulfilling coach
Jim Donnan's primary mission this year: increase turnovers.
(Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   FB-FALCONS _ How have contract issues affected this team? The
timing of some extensions has rankled some players and agents.
(Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-BENSON _ Johnny Benson says he is not panicking yet, even
though he still doesn't have a ride for next season and most of the
prime jobs already have been filled. Benson is parting ways with
Roush Racing after the Atlanta race because of back-to-back
disappointing years. What went wrong? What is he going to do about
next season? (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet NASCAR page for the week.
</P>
