   COXNET NASCAR 1021 -- Johnny Benson says he is not panicking
yet, even though he still doesn't have a ride for next season and
most of the prime jobs already have been filled. Benson is parting
ways with Roush Racing after the Atlanta race because of
back-to-back disappointing years. What went wrong? What is he going
to do about next season? (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   WINSTON CUP NOTES: Odds and ends column from the world of
Winston Cup. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BUSCH SERIES NOTES: Odds and ends column from the world of Busch
series. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WINSTON CUP STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   BUSCH GRAND NATIONAL STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   NEXT RACE -- A preview of Sunday's Pop Secret Microwave Popcorn
400 from North Carolina Motor Speedway featuring a 2-column color
illustration of North Carolina Motor Speedway, Rockingham, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-THRASHERS _ Andrew Brunette only had 11 goals last season
with Nashville, but he already has four for the Thrashers in just
six games. Three of the goals have come on the power play. What has
turned Brunette into such a goal scorer? (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
