<SLUG> BC-STYLE-EMUOIL22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Skin line sells like oil off an emu's back
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Not to ruffle any feathers, but compared
with graceful swans, regal eagles or Technicolor parrots, emus
aren't the most aesthetically pleasing members of the bird kingdom.
</P>
<P>
   Which makes the cosmetic use of emu oil _ in its unrefined state
a foul-smelling, pale yellow substance from a thick pad of fat on
the bird's back _ all the more ironic.
</P>
<P>
   Miami Beach's Planet Emu is one of several companies banking on
emu oil to emerge as the next aloe vera. W magazine recently called
it a prime ingredient of the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
   Planet Emu launched its line of seven Dremu products last
November, and it's now available in more than 100 department stores
and about 50 spas, boutiques and dermatologists' offices
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's sold as a skin-care product, but it actually is a
therapeutic product,'' says company President Julie Brumlik.
</P>
<P>
   Dremu is the only cosmetic line in department stores that
contains emu oil in every product, she says, although other
companies such as Donna Karan Cosmetics include emu oil in some of
their formulas.
</P>
<P>
   On the thousands of emu farms in the United States, and the
roughly 200 in Florida, emus are raised primarily as a low-fat,
iron-rich alternative to red meat. The flightless bird's oil ``has
the closest composition to the original oil that is in human skin
of any oil that we know,'' Brumlik says.
</P>
<P>
   But whoever thought to use emu oil?
</P>
<P>
   The ancient Aborigines, actually, who discovered its benefits
centuries before modern scientists. According to Planet Emu and the
American Emu Association, the oil is a natural emollient that
penetrates seven layers of skin and acts as a carrier for
anti-oxidants, vitamin C and other skin-care ingredients. Absorbed
quickly, it helps the skin retain moisture and rebalances the
fatty-acid composition in older skin, making it appear plumper and
therefore younger.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dermabrasion and acid peels are rough ways to resurface the
skin,'' Brumlik says. ``Emu oil is a more gentle, modern way to do
the same thing. ... You don't have to have pain to get the gain
from it.''
</P>
<P>
   Emu oil also is anti-inflammatory. Dremu recommends its Pain
Relief Extra Strength Thermal Therapy, a mix of 40 percent pure emu
oil and nine other analgesic oils, as an antidote to sore muscles
and stiff joints.
</P>
<P>
   ``The variety and number of skin conditions that we're able to
improve has turned out to be sort of astounding,'' says Brumlik,
adding that it's all backed by clinical research.
</P>
<P>
   But Ira Schlesinger, a Delray Beach dermatologist, says emus
haven't shown their memorable mugs in the scientific literature.
</P>
<P>
   ``As far as I can tell, it fits into the category of what's new
for the month,'' Schlesinger says. ``In the dermatological
journals, there's no current mention of anything that's been proven
with that product. ... I am not aware of any scientific data of
(emu oil) doing anything other than moisturizing.''
</P>
<P>
   And that's not all bad. ``Moisturizing makes all skin look
better,'' Schlesinger says. ``It temporarily makes wrinkles and
aging skin look better. ... But true value comes beyond that, in
changing the structural components of the skin, and I'm not aware
of any evidence that that occurs (with emu oil).''
</P>
<P>
   Customers seem to like the stuff, though. Brumlik says after
Vogue magazine published a story, department stores started
calling.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike the perpetually grounded emu, Dremu sales took flight.
</P>
<P>
   THE MANY FACES OF EMU
</P>
<P>
   Dremu's emu-oil products include:
</P>
<P>
   _ Daylight Age Defying Lotion: daily moisturizer with Vitamin C
and SPF 15. $38 for 2 oz.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cashmere: hand and body lotion with ylang-ylang. $30 for 8 oz.
</P>
<P>
   _ Airbrush Refining Eye Cream: ceramides, elastin, collagen and
green tea extract to reduce puffiness. $38 for 0.5 oz.
</P>
<P>
   _ Whistle Moisturizing Facial Cleanser: nonfoaming cleanser with
Japanese grapefruit scent. $22 for 8 oz.
</P>
<P>
   You can order Dremu by calling (800) 373-4011 or by visiting
www.dremu.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
