movies that define every decade ...'' Yeah, there are, but ``Body
Shots'' isn't one of them, unless you've spent the decade with your
nose buried in magazine sex-advice columns. This overdirected,
pretentious film has about as much depth as an average ``Friends''
episode, although come to think of it, ``Friends'' is more
decade-defining, even with its well-chronicled lack of diversity.
