<P>
   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Greeks were wrong. Long ago, Aristotle, Socrates
and Plato decided that arguing was the best method of thinking, and
the more critical you could be, the better. Westerners adopted
their ideas like they were written in stone and have been arguing
in conference rooms, offices and factory floors ever since. Since
then, many different methods of thinking have been conceived, but
few have such a documented track record as the one developed by the
world renowned conceptual thinker Edward De Bono and his ``Six
Thinking Hats.'' Before you dismiss this as some sequel by Dr.
Suess, consider what companies around the globe have accomplished
since the Six Thinking Hats method was first described in his book
14 years ago. By TERESA MCUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial
category. &QL; 
