</P>
<P>
   OPEC-CARTEL (Undated) _ Left for dead two years ago, the oil
cartel is back, in a new, potentially more powerful form. Oil
prices have risen and stayed high because of an unprecedented
cooperation between Saudi Arabia and two non-Opec members, Mexico
and Norway. The three have informally set production quotas that,
unlike OPEC's formal attempts at quotas, have actually stuck, and
lots of other countries, recognizing a good thing when they see it,
are going along. By Agis Salpukas.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-PLANNING (Undated) _ It's quite a come-on: Be your own
travel agent and save a bundle! Complete kit for just $500! Our
jaundice-eyed reporter tries it to see. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-WATCH (New York) _ A weekly feature looking at
developments of the market worldwide. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
