<P>
   GORE-ENVIRON (Rye, N.H.) _ In the most dramatic proposal of his
candidacy, Vice President Al Gore says that as president he would
ban any new offshore drilling for oil and gas along the California
and Florida coasts. Gore's proposal would apply to companies that
have already bought billions of dollars worth of leases and not
drilled yet. By Katharine Q. Seelye. (We plan to move the story by
8:30 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
