   reefer to: BRADLEY-POVERTY (Undated) _ Describing poverty as a
``slow motion national disaster,'' former Sen. Bill Bradley calls
for reducing the number of poor children by half over the coming
decade by raising the minimum wage, increasing spending on child
care programs and providing an array of tax benefits to poor
parents who work. By James Dao. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET
in ``p'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
