   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   CHILD-CARE (Washington) _ Good early-childhood education has a
powerful impact that lasts into young adulthood, affecting
everything from reading and mathematics skills to the timing of
child-bearing, researchers announce, citing the first study ever to
track participants from infancy to age 21. By Jodi Wilgoren.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
