<HEADLINE>
USC ANNOUNCES PLANS FOR NEW ARENA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ As previously reported, USC officials announced
plans Thursday to build a 12,000-seat campus-events center that
they expect to be completed by January, 2002.
</P>
<P>
   The facility is planned to be located across the street from the
campus, on the corner of Figueroa Street and Jefferson Boulevard,
where a parking lot exists. But athletic director Mike Garrett said
a final decision on the location has not been made.
</P>
<P>
   Garrett has assured USC president Steven B. Sample that the
arena will cost under $70 million. Construction is expected to
begin this summer. Sample said ground will not be broken until 100
percent of the funds have been pledged.
</P>
<P>
   It is believed at least $12 million has been raised, but Garrett
said Thursday's announcement was the official kickoff to
fund-raising.
</P>
<P>
   Sample could be a huge ally in fund-raising. Under his tenure,
USC has become the only university to secure three individual
donations of $100 million or more.
</P>
<P>
   ``(The arena) is substantially smaller than that,'' Sample said.
``It will be important to get a huge lead gift of $10-20 million.''
</P>
<P>
   USC's basketball coaches were elated by the announcement,
particularly women's coach Chris Gobrecht.
</P>
<P>
   ``How do I feel?,'' Gobrecht said. ``How would Superman feel if
kryptonite never existed? To know we can never be stopped again is
an incredible feeling.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is not a reason for the best players to come to USC, but it
will be a place to inspire great players and an appropriate place
to showcase their talents.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not something to keep up with our cross-town rival. We
don't have to do something this hard to keep up with those guys.
It's something we know will put them to shame. Not that we're into
that.''
</P>
<P>
   USC has hired HNTB Sports Architecture, a company that
specializes in arena design, to begin developing architectural
specifications. An architect and contractor will be selected next
year.
</P>
<P>
   Garrett said an outside marketing firm would be hired to obtain
naming rights to the facility. USC has already met with GTE on the
subject.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the most important project ever undertaken by the
athletic department,'' Garrett said. ``I believe some of us have
been waiting for 50 years for this.''
</P>
<P>
   As usual, men's basketball coach Henry Bibby provided the best
moment of levity about the arena.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very happy to be the first men's basketball coach in the
new arena,'' Bibby said. ``We hope. Right, Mike?''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-21-99 2157EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
