<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Falcons' infirmary empty
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ With the season the Falcons have had, Thursday was
like a vacation for trainer Ron Medlin.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time since the first day of training camp that
every player on the active roster practiced. No wonder Medlin kept
walking when that was mentioned to him.
</P>
<P>
   He didn't want to jinx anything after linebackers Jessie Tuggle
(strained left patella tendon), Keith Brooking (sprained right
knee), and Henri Crockett (swelling in left knee) returned after
not practicing Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Tuggle, reserve safety Johndale Carty (strained left hamstring),
and Brooking _ who all missed last Sunday's game _ are still listed
as doubtful for Monday's game at Pittsburgh (3-3).
</P>
<P>
   But in a 1-5 season where starters have missed nine games,
All-Pro running back Jamal Anderson (knee surgery) is out for the
season, and quarterback Chris Chandler has missed three games and
parts of the other three, it's OK to dream, isn't it?
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not as confident ... because we haven't been able to
work together much,'' coach Dan Reeves said.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Defensive end) Chuck Smith (who sprained his right big toe on
the first day of camp) is close to 100 percent, Chris (Chandler,
who has battled a right hamstring injury) was better than in a long
time. Hopefully, you can go through a game that way.''
</P>
<P>
   Tuggle had to readjust the wrap on his left leg, and Brooking
split time with Craig Sauer. But progress is progress.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you have your whole team out there,'' Brooking said,
``that definitely gives the team more confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   Reserves also have been hit. Defensive tackle Ed Jasper, who
will play Monday, missed the past three games with a left knee
injury. Punt and kickoff returner Tim Dwight, who will start at
wide receiver, missed two games with a right hamstring injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``It helps to see the entire corps out there,'' said cornerback
Michael Booker, who missed the first three games with a right thigh
injury. ``You can practice all the packages. It's a pick up.''
</P>
<P>
   In training camp, running back Gary Downs and rookie center Todd
McClure suffered season-ending knee injuries, and tight end O.J.
Santiago missed two weeks after being thrown from a golf cart.
</P>
<P>
   Wide receivers Dwight, Chris Calloway, Terance Mathis, Ronnie
Harris and Jammi German all missed practice with injuries. Smith
missed nearly three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Medlin's staff couldn't rest Thursday, however.
</P>
<P>
   Chuck Connor, director of pro player personnel, was stung by a
wasp and had to be treated.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
