<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Oct. 22 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories please contact Lori Stassi at (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-ALZHEIMER'S (Los Angeles) _ Researchers for Amgen Inc. and
the Harvard Medical School will publish an article in today's
edition of the journal Science that identifies a compound key to
the formation of plaques that the researchers say are the cause of
Alzheimer's disease. The discovery _ which a spokesman for the
Thousand Oaks-based biotech giant called ``the Holy Grail'' of
Alzheimer's research _ could lead to the formulation of a drug to
inhibit those compounds. By Jason Cohen (will move on the ``a''
national, ``n'' California and ``f'' financial news wires)
</P>
<P>
   MONTE-BANKRUPTCY (Los Angeles) _ Monte McKeon, one of five
McKeon brothers that oversaw the expansion and eventual bankruptcy
of the Howard &AMP; Phil's Western Wear chain, filed for personal
bankruptcy this week, citing more than $100,000 in credit card
bills spread over a dozen cards. One of McKeon's brothers is
Congressman Howard ``Buck'' McKeon, a Republican from Santa
Clarita. By Jason Takenouchi (will move in the ``f'' financial news
wire)
</P>
<P>
   CSUN-SHOWBIZ (Los Angeles) _ Cal State Northridge, as part of an
ongoing campaign to establish itself as a Hollywood player, holds a
one-day seminar on Friday to ``demystify'' the economics of show
business through its Entertainment Industry Institute. By Dave
McNary (will move in the ``f'' financial news wire)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-CAMPUS (Los Angeles) _ The city of Glendale has initiated
the process of collecting information from agencies regarding Walt
Disney Co.'s Creative Campus, giving the project an official start.
If completed as proposed, Disney would turn an old airfield into a
huge campus that would employ thousands of workers. By Dave McNary
(will move in the ``f'' financial news wire)
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
