<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Oct. 22. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MCCAIN _ Working to patch his relations with environmentalists,
Arizona Sen. John McCain on Thursday removed language in a bill
that could have allowed a noisy air-tour ``free-for-all'' over
Grand Canyon National Park. The Republican presidential candidate
dropped a plan that could have automatically allowed all air-tour
aircraft to be considered ``quiet.'' By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
